body:
When dealing with complex struct structures, such as combinations of arrays and structs

For example:

- An array where each element is a struct
- A struct where one of its elements is an array
- Mixed case


```
typedef struct {
    rand bit [7:0] byte_array[5];
    rand int int_array[5];
    bit [7:0] non_rand_byte_array[5];
} ArrayStruct;

typedef struct {
    rand bit [7:0] byte_value;
    rand int int_value;
} UnpackedStruct;

typedef struct {
    rand UnpackedStruct unpacked_array[5];
} UnpackedArrayStruct;
```

There are issues with handling constrained randomization in these cases.

We are working on this.

